Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.14,0:00:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as people are\Ninvolved in modern-day crimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.19,0:00:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are no unsolvable mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.85,0:00:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case is about\Na mysterious murder weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's use our heads\Nto figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.40,0:00:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.12,0:00:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.18,0:00:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.09,0:01:57.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Case of the\NMysterious Murder Weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Case of the\NMysterious Murder Weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:02:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice to take a leisurely\Nwalk together once in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.05,0:02:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.55,0:02:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so fun about\Nwalking with that runt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.98,0:02:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.07,0:02:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.82,0:02:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little bird...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.15,0:02:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.49,0:02:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It looks okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.37,0:02:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't seem to be hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.71,0:02:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It flew off...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.88,0:02:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a weird bird. Maybe\Nit had an anemic attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.13,0:02:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming from\Nthat apartment building!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.39,0:02:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are only two\Napartments occupied here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:02:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just heard a woman\Nscream from this building!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.20,0:03:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?\NI didn't hear anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back. You're back early.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.75,0:03:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, these folks here--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.00,0:03:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.51,0:03:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's horrible! My husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was\Nmurdered on our veranda!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Detective Mori.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.10,0:03:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it you're\Nthe one who screamed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.18,0:03:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which room is yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.60,0:03:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Room 715.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, I looked at\Nthe mail board earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.74,0:03:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hardly anybody lives here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.53,0:03:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place is going to\Nbe demolished this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.91,0:03:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the only ones living here now
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.41,0:03:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are Imoto, who runs his own business,\Nand Terasawa-{\i1}san {\i0}here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.88,0:03:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.76,0:04:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High heels and two\Npairs of men's shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:20.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Real Estate Agent\NRyusuke Imoto, 39 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been hit in the back of the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.95,0:04:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder weapon appears to\Nhave been a flower pot or the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.28,0:04:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Dobashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.00,0:04:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you kill him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the cause of death was brain damage...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.59,0:04:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer most likely lifted\Nup a flower pot from behind him
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.14,0:04:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and brought it down\Nas hard as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.60,0:04:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.85,0:04:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a mark here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:05:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe it has something\Nto do with the murder--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.11,0:05:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you ever learn to stop\Nbutting in during our investigations?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.20,0:05:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There definitely is a mark here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.08,0:05:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems extremely new\Ncompared to all the other marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.46,0:05:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was Mr. Ryusuke\NImoto, 39 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.47,0:05:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and president of NEED,\Na real estate agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.47,0:05:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was his wife, Takako-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nwho found him. Correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.43,0:05:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.81,0:05:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the person found\Nstanding in front of the body
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.48,0:05:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when Mori-{\i1}kun {\i0}and\Nthe others came rushing in...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Dobashi.\NI manage an import company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.90,0:05:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Imoto-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s former boss and\Nthe one who introduced him to his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.82,0:05:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to see him today\Nabout a business matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His matchmaker, eh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.29,0:05:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:06:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terasawa. I live on\Nthe 5th floor of this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.75,0:06:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to run a fishing goods store.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.63,0:06:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Used to"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.21,0:06:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Imoto took control of my store!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.97,0:06:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used some dirty\Nlegal loophole to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.05,0:06:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a terrible man!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.35,0:06:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is he did the same\Nsort of things to these people too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.19,0:06:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.90,0:06:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.94,0:06:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As their matchmaker,\NI shouldn't be saying this,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.86,0:06:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he and his wife were in\Nthe middle of getting divorced
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there was trouble\Nabout the compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.08,0:06:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that wouldn't matter if he died--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.49,0:06:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she'd get his inheritance instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.16,0:06:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.75,0:06:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard my husband constantly\Nrefused your requests for a loan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.29,0:06:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because your company was on\Nthe verge of going out of business!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.25,0:06:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you couldn't\Nhandle it and killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.47,0:06:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. Calm down, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.18,0:06:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Apartment Manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.97,0:06:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that main door the only way\Nin and out of this building?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.89,0:07:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.10,0:07:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only ones who\Nentered besides the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.15,0:07:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...were his wife, Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nand Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.57,0:07:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, each of you had a\Ndecent enough motive to kill the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.37,0:07:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, one of\Nyou three murdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.62,0:07:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.54,0:07:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First you, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.13,0:07:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please explain the situation\Nwhen you found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.63,0:07:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a little after 5:00\Nwhen I arrived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.76,0:07:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More precisely,\Nit was just after 5:05.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.31,0:07:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I record when everyone\Nenters or leaves the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be very handy for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.40,0:07:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.36,0:07:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I came here today
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.53,0:07:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was to discuss the compensation\Nwith my husband one more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just as Dobashi-{\i1}san {\i0}mentioned earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He and I have been living\Napart for quite a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.50,0:08:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.16,0:08:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my husband was practicing\NTai Chi on the veranda by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.50,0:08:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tai Chi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.79,0:08:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.84,0:08:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband did it every\Nmorning and evening for his health.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.01,0:08:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't notice\Nwhen I entered the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.26,0:08:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I didn't call out to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.85,0:08:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I looked out the veranda\Nagain after using the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.98,0:08:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my husband was dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.52,0:08:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So basically, your husband died\Nwhile you were in the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.49,0:08:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon my asking, but how\Nlong were you in the bathroom for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.62,0:08:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only about two minutes, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.16,0:08:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means your husband\Ndied at approximately 5:08.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While you were in the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.29,0:08:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,did you hear any\Nsounds or people talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.34,0:08:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.84,0:08:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, when you entered the apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.35,0:09:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were there any shoes by the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.89,0:09:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, just a pair of my husband's shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.98,0:09:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you, Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.19,0:09:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around what time did you first arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.94,0:09:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little before 5:00, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was to meet with Imoto-{\i1}kun\N{\i0}at 5 o'clock, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.99,0:09:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More precisely, 4:58.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.41,0:09:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as his wife said,\Nthe reason I came here
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.42,0:09:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was to ask for a loan one last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.88,0:09:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pointless,\Nno matter how hard you try!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.09,0:09:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no desire\Nor reason to help you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.55,0:09:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now please leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.60,0:09:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I went to the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.94,0:09:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.44,0:09:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stood there for a while, in a daze.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.36,0:10:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was then that I heard her scream\Nfrom the other side of the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.04,0:10:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when I rushed into the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.12,0:10:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Imoto-{\i1}san {\i0}was dead\Non the veranda, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.88,0:10:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.59,0:10:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.38,0:10:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I have to do with it?\NI wasn't in the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.51,0:10:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just need to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around what time did\Nyou leave the building?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.39,0:10:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it was\Na little before 5:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.23,0:10:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,4:50, to be precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.69,0:10:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he didn't\Nreturn until just after 5:12.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.90,0:10:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"But"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He came back from his golf\Npractice rather earlier than usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.99,0:10:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I changed my mind on the way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.00,0:10:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been a\Nbit spur-of-the-moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.42,0:10:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.84,0:11:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.01,0:11:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't in the building\Nwhen Imoto-{\i1}san {\i0}was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.18,0:11:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you're not the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.39,0:11:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The issue here is with\Nhis wife and Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.85,0:11:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First you, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you found your husband's\Nbody after you left the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.36,0:11:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's the possibility that\Nyou never went to the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that you killed your husband,\Npretended to find him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.33,0:11:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then screamed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.70,0:11:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.29,0:11:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you went up to the roof
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.29,0:11:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after Imoto-{\i1}san {\i0}refused\Nto lend you money,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.21,0:11:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's a possibility\Nyou were actually in his office
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or with him on the veranda!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you can see from here\Nis a small part of the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.43,0:11:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also possible\Nthat when his wife came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you were on the\Nveranda or in his office,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.64,0:11:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,killed the victim while\Nshe was in the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.36,0:11:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then went up to the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.27,0:11:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.61,0:12:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was already on the roof by\Nthe time she came in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.74,0:12:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She even said that only\NImoto-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s shoes were by the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also possible that\Nshe didn't remember correctly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.16,0:12:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you have proof that you\Nwere on the roof the whole time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.67,0:12:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.38,0:12:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there was no one on the roof, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.92,0:12:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I heard a sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.76,0:12:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A sound?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.26,0:12:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was a loud, metallic sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.43,0:12:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It came from the\Narea around this veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.22,0:12:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard a sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.43,0:12:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. A metallic one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.81,0:12:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, could that sound have been\Nsomething hitting the handrail?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.82,0:12:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, there's a fresh mark on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears something\Nhit it from below...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.95,0:12:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! That's the sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The marks look similar...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.38,0:13:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the other mark\Nwas made coming up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no question\Nthat someone hit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear the sound, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.39,0:13:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I probably didn't hear it\Nbecause I was in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.52,0:13:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.14,0:13:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would someone put\Na mark in a place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.57,0:13:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes no sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.48,0:13:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This handrail seems suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.69,0:13:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but in my opinion none of\Nthem seem to be lying, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.95,0:13:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.24,0:13:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just because Dobashi heard\Na sound from the handrail
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.24,0:13:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that isn't proof that\Nhe was on the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.50,0:13:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He or the victim\Nmight've made the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.91,0:13:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while he was on the veranda!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.00,0:13:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if the\Nkiller was someone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.17,0:13:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that means they flew in\Nlike a bird to kill the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.34,0:13:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then flew off the exact\Nsame way they came!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.93,0:13:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which would never, ever happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do have a point...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bird? A bird?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,\Nthe spot where the bird fell--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.24,0:14:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--was over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.91,0:14:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Directly in front of the\Nmark on this handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.70,0:14:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The location where\Nthe victim collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The location where the bird fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.75,0:14:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mark on the handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.42,0:14:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An abandoned building\Nacross the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.09,0:14:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the killer's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.01,0:14:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder weapon\Nwasn't a flower pot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.89,0:14:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer was that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.93,0:14:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My deductions\Ncan't possibly be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.52,0:14:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's his wife,\Nwho lives separately from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.52,0:14:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the president\Nof an import company.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.82,0:14:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's the former owner\Nof a fishing goods store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the killer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.62,0:14:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.91,0:14:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be returning\Nto my apartment now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.87,0:14:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.54,0:15:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can go for today...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.50,0:15:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let that happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.75,0:15:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to make the\Nold man realize it somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.43,0:15:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you figured\Nanything out, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.78,0:15:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, you may\Nleave, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.99,0:15:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.20,0:15:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going to happen to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.07,0:15:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.62,0:15:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.81,0:15:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, realize it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.56,0:16:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.36,0:16:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the spot where\Nthe victim collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.11,0:16:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the mark on the handrail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.49,0:16:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan, that bird\Nfell down there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.37,0:16:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.75,0:16:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.38,0:16:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim, the mark, that bird,\Nand that abandoned building!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all directly lined up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know who did it, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.39,0:16:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.68,0:16:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get too ahead of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.60,0:16:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain everything atop\Nthat abandoned building!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.19,0:16:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.50,0:17:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.38,0:17:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you checking\Nfor in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see what this\Nhas to do with the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.18,0:17:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone gather around here, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.98,0:17:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, allow me to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.44,0:17:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0},\NTerasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have any of you\Never been here before?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.15,0:17:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.15,0:17:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.15,0:17:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor have I.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.45,0:17:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see the victim's\Nveranda from here, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.58,0:17:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but what does that\Nhave to do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever heard\Nof surf casting, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.55,0:17:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surf casting?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.01,0:17:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a type of fishing that\Nuses a so-called "spinning reel"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.14,0:18:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to allow the fisher to cast the\Nline some dozens of meters out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.97,0:18:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used\Nthis technique from here
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.39,0:18:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to hit the victim's head with a\Nweight as he stood on the veranda!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.52,0:18:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.48,0:18:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This footprint is the proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.57,0:18:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The left foot is in front\Nand with a lot of weight on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.45,0:18:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was made when the killer\Nflung the pole in an overhand fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.71,0:18:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.25,0:18:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he was killed,\Nthe victim was performing Tai Chi,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.01,0:18:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is known\Nfor its slow movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.55,0:18:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer swung the fishing\Npole when he turned away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.56,0:18:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And as it was reeled in--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.07,0:18:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--the weight hit the handrail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.82,0:19:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's the sound I heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.53,0:19:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.78,0:19:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer didn't realize the weight\Nhad left a mark when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.00,0:19:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there was one other\Nmiscalculation on the killer's part.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.08,0:19:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the weight was being\Nreeled in, it hit a bird in mid-air.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.30,0:19:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bird you picked up had\Nprobably received a concussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}, it's over\Nthirty meters to that veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.69,0:19:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could someone really cast a\Nweight that far with such precision?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With enough practice, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.32,0:19:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially for someone\Nwho's good at surf casting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.74,0:19:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.41,0:19:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those shoes you're wearing right now
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.91,0:19:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,should undoubtedly\Nmatch these footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.58,0:19:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if we look hard enough\Naround this abandoned building,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.25,0:19:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll probably--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.34,0:20:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! There's something\Non the ground here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.64,0:20:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what this is!\NIt's a pole grip!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pole grip?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.43,0:20:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes after fishermen\Nconnect fishing rods together,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.15,0:20:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they won't come undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.02,0:20:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So to prevent their\Nhands from slipping,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.15,0:20:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they place rubber tubes or rubber\Nbands near where the rods connect,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.82,0:20:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then pull the rods apart while\Ntwisting them in opposite directions!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty smart to know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to see it\Non a TV fishing show yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.83,0:20:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, they had their\Ngloves off when they used these.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.96,0:20:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because they would slip!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the killer's\Nfingerprints should be on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.67,0:20:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}. Your fingerprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.89,0:20:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help but laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.14,0:20:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He took over my store
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and said he was going to build\Na fashion building in its place!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:21:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I'd give up ownership\Nif he'd just spare the store, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.32,0:21:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in keeping\Nthis dinky store around.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.16,0:21:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so fun about\Ncatching fish, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.75,0:21:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you losers\Nsee in it at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.18,0:21:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My precious fishing rod!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He destroyed it\Nbefore my very eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.48,0:21:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I absolutely couldn't\Nlet him get away with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.62,0:23:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your detective work last\Nnight was amazing, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.74,0:23:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My opinion of you\Nkeeps getting better!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.82,0:23:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cases like that are\Na piece of cake for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.83,0:23:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he actually\Nmake that fishing rod toy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.61,0:23:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make me realize it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.56,0:23:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got something!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.67,0:23:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.61,0:23:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.57,0:23:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.65,0:23:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who am I kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.00,0:24:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back here, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.77,0:24:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy's one of the men in black!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.40,0:24:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.26,0:24:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go before\Nthe bomber gets away!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.79,0:24:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! So that's how it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.83,0:24:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the eyes of the killer,\Nthis was an unexpected murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.40,0:24:31.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Game Company Murder Case
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.99,0:24:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.41,0:24:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Game Company Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.08,0:24:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.47,0:24:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cloakroom Tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.77,0:24:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode the men in \Nblack make an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.89,0:24:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan, I'll return to my adult form, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.70,0:24:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
